la]] selected to play the leading female role.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.apunkachoice.com/scoop/downsouth/tamil/20050906-0.html |title=Laila is back in Kollywood with a bang : Down South : Tamil News |publisher=ApunKaChoice.Com |date=26 January 2006 |accessdate=18 October 2012}}</ref> The film was launched on 10 September 2005 by [[Rajinikanth]], while the title was changed to ''Paramasivan''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/features/News/News29/10-9-05e/tamil-movies-news-ajith.html |title=Tamil movies : It will be Paramasivan from P Vasu |publisher=Behindwoods |date=10 September 2005 |accessdate=18 October 2012}}</ref>\n\nFollowing [[Ajith Kumar]]'s exit from Bala's directorial venture, ''[[Naan Kadavul]]'', this film changed producers the next month with S. Ramesh Babu agreeing to finance the film. [[Nisha Kothari]] was first requested to appear in an [[item number]] in the film but the role was later taken by [[Ragasya]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ajithkumar.free.fr/news/news_189.htm |title=\"Jay Jay\" Amoga In Paramasivan? |publisher=www.ajithkumar.fr.fm |date=21 September 2005  |accessdate=18 October 2012}}</ref> For the film, Ajith Kumar lost fifteen kilograms to get into shape.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/jan/11vasu.htm |title=P Vasu: Ready for Paramasivan |publisher=Rediff|date= |accessdate=18 October 2012}}</ref> [[K. Balachandar]]'s Kavithalaya Productions took up the distribution of ''Paramasivan'' for the Chengalpet area.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/19707.html |title=A new role for old man&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil Movie News |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=13 January 2006 |accessdate=18 October 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n\nBackground score and Songs composed by [[Vidyasagar (music director)|Vidyasagar]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tamilsonglyrics.org/movies/p-t/paramasivan-songs-lyrics/|title=Paramasivan songs lyrics |work=tamilsonglyrics|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150623222731/http://www.tamilsonglyrics.org/movies/p-t/paramasivan-songs-lyrics/|archivedate=23 June 2015}}</ref>\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Paramasivan\n| type       = soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Vidyasagar (music director)|Vidyasagar]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 2 January 2006\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[World Music]]\n| length     =\n| label      = The Best Audio\n| producer   = [[Vidyasagar (music director)|Vidyasagar]]\n| prev_title = [[Thambi (2006 film)|Thambi]]\n| prev_year  = 2006\n| next_title = [[Aathi]]\n| next_year  = 2006\n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:70%;\"\n|-\n! Song Title !! Singers !! Lyrics\n|-\n| ''Oru Kili'' || [[Madhu Balakrishnan]], [[Sujatha Mohan|Sujatha]] || [[Yugabharathi]]\n|-\n| ''Aasai Dosai'' || Priya Subramani || [[Na. Muthukumar]]\n|-\n| ''Kannan'' || Kalyani Menon, Lakshmi Rangarajan, [[Saindhavi]] || Kirithaya\n|-\n| ''Natchathira Paravaikku'' || [[Tippu (singer)|Tippu]], Rajalakshmi || [[Vairamuthu]]\n|-\n| ''Thangakkili'' || [[Madhu Balakrishnan]], [[Gopika Poornima]], Srivarthini || Kirithaya\n|-\n| ''Undivila'' || [[Shankar Mahadevan]], [[Malathy Lakshman]] || [[P. Vijay]]\n|-\n| ''Paramasivane'' || [[Shankar Mahadevan]], Chandran, [[Karthik (singer)|Karthik]], [[Tippu (singer)|Tippu]], Jemon, [[Ranjith (singer)|Ranjith]] || [[Vairamuthu]]\n|-\n| ''Theme'' || Instrumental\n|}\n\n==Release==\nThe satellite rights of the film were sold to [[Jaya TV]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.in.com/tv/movies/jaya-tv-147/paramasivan-41367.html|title=LIVE TV - Watch Indian TV Channels - Live Streaming and Catchup TV - LIVE News Online - in.com|website=in.com}}</ref> It was dubbed into Hindi as ''Godfather Shiva''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9UryKHYuoNY|title=YouTube|website=www.youtube.com}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|Film|India}}\n* [[List of action films of the 2000s]]\n* [[List of Tamil films of 2006]]\n{{clear}}\n\n==References=